==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enslave
<hw>En*slave"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Enslaved</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Enslaving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To reduce to slavery;
to make a slave of; to subject to a dominant influence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The conquer'd, also, and <qex>enslaved</qex> by war,⟦br⟧
Shall, with their freedom lost, all virtue lose.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pleasure admitted in undue degree⟦br⟧
<qex>Enslaves</qex> the will.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enslavedness</ent>⟦br⟧
